                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Milow_FV wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I dont see a lot of added value for the 2nd lvl of sooth, MoM, and Statis.  I have alot of aa's and I am looking at getting Delay death and the added increases to my resist over the 2nd lvl of statis and MoM.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Extra levels of sooth are very useful as they increase the amount of damage reduction rather significantly.  If you find level 1 useful then you will find levels 2 and 3 invaluable.
<br />

<br />
MoM is an interesting one.  I think subsequent levels of this should have been more efficient for a given period of time.  As it is, level 1 lets you absorb 10 hits against your mana instead of your hit points.  Even against a mob that 'only' hits for 500, that is 5,000 mana at just level 1 (and most mobs hit for more than 500.  Level 2 may have marginal use if you are someone who thinks you can time a gather mana in there somewhere.  I can't imagine what good level 3 would be.
<br />

<br />
Extra levels of stasis are just a convenience.  I have it maxxed, and it is nice to know you can basically forget about a mob once you hit it.  In EQ, 3 minutes is an eternity.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
